  "verdict": "BedMachine direct phi-free N REPRODUCES the marine-West gating (interaction d=-0.035 CI[-0.052,-0.019], d ln u_*/dTF +0.62/degC near flotation vs +0.46/degC well grounded); the Bedmap2-rel proxy gives d=-0.100 CI[-0.122,-0.078]. The effective-pressure reading is robust to a more-direct, independent N.",
  "caveats": "N assumes an ocean-connected hydraulic head at the bed (the relevant limit near grounding lines); truly-measured N needs boreholes/seismic. n_hat is the most-direct N obtainable from open gridded geometry. Speed/N are correlated (fast ice rides near flotation); the interaction term controls main effects, not every confound; bootstrap CIs ignore spatial autocorrelation."
